    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1973-06-28T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1973-06-28T00:00:00-05:00" n="138"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d138">
                <head>138. National Security Decision Memorandum 224<note n="1" type="source"
                        xml:id="d138fn1">Source: National Archives, Nixon Presidential Materials,
                            <gloss target="#t_NSC_1">NSC</gloss> Files, Box 364, Subject Files,
                        NSDMs Nos. 145–264. Secret. A copy was sent to <persName corresp="#p_MTH_1"
                            >Moorer</persName>.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1973-06-28">June 28, 1973</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <list>
                    <head>TO</head>
                    <item>The Secretary of State</item>
                    <item>The Acting Secretary of Defense</item>
                    <item>The Director of Central Intelligence</item>
                </list>
                <list type="subject">
                    <head>SUBJECT</head>
                    <item>National Net Assessment Process, <gloss target="#t_NSSM_1">NSSM</gloss>
                        178</item>
                </list>
                <p>The President, upon review of the paper prepared and submitted in compliance with
                        <gloss target="#t_NSSM_1">NSSM</gloss> 178<note n="2" xml:id="d138fn2">
                        <ref target="#d136">Document 136</ref>.</note> and the comments of the
                        <gloss target="#t_NSCIC_1">NSCIC</gloss> Principals thereon, has approved
                    the recommendations of the Ad Hoc Group and wishes to proceed with a program of
                    national net assessment. To this end:</p>
                <p>—A permanent Net Assessment Standing Committee is established, having
                    representation from the Departments of State and Defense, and the Director of
                    Central Intelligence, and chaired by a representative of the National Security
                    Council Staff.</p>
                <p>—Requests for net assessments will be issued as National Security Study
                    Memoranda.</p>
                <pb facs="0681" n="639" xml:id="pg_639"/>
                <p>—Net assessments prepared in accordance with these <gloss target="#t_NSSM_1"
                        >NSSM</gloss>s will be forwarded to the Chairman of the <gloss
                        target="#t_NSCIC_1">NSCIC</gloss> for review by that Committee.</p>
                <p>Addressees should forward to me the names of their representatives to the Net
                    Assessment Standing Committee.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_KHA_1">Henry A. Kissinger</persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
